<?xml version="1.0"?>
<Fleet xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">
  <Name>Green Wing</Name>
  <Version>3</Version>
  <TotalPoints>3000</TotalPoints>
  <FactionKey>KUIPER/kuiper</FactionKey>
  <Description>Difficulty: &lt;color=yellow&gt;MODERATE&lt;/color&gt;

Green Wing is a wing centered around Ambush Tactics, Map Denial, and Point Capture.
Composed of 3 Particle Lance Destroyers, and six skirmishing corvettes equipped with castle turrets to contest other small ships. There is one expendable corvette designed for driving onto commonly contested capture points to secure an early advantage, generally the 'A' capture point.

The Void Stalker, Void Walker, and Void Lurker Particle Lance Destroyers are designed to wait, only jumping out of corners to deny prospecting enemy cappers. When the opportunity presents itself, these Destroyers may be used to destroy enemy capital ships. When doing this, keep in mind the damage will decrease with your range to the target, so get close to maximise damage potential.

The Kyve Corvettes are designed to quickly dart onto caps and evade enemy fire, only going for open cap points when it is safe, and peppering at enemy missiles and cappers when possible. These corvettes also mount several CBU-40 Cubesat, able to provide soft kill or extra point defense in a pinch to their mothership. They cannot be landed once launched, so think carefully before deploying one. Generally, you will deploy one "Point Defense" loadout before entering a capture point to defend against enemy cruise missiles.

The "They Deserved Worse" will generally deploy a Point Defense cubesat before entering the 'A' capture point. If it survives, return it to a safe spot for later use in other dangerous capture attempts, to minimise losses.
  </Description>
  <SortOverrideOrder>6</SortOverrideOrder>
  <ModDependencies>
    <unsignedLong>3649434947</unsignedLong>
  </ModDependencies>
